title: ​820-2914 - Won't turn on
message: You said the fan was spinning, for that to happen 5V_S0 must at least be there for the duration that the fan is on. Again your measurements don't make sense. U5750/55 getting hot is not a good sign, they are powered off 3V42 so they must always be hot then. If they really get hot and it is not a cap near them you can remove U5750/55, they are not needed for the board to power on for now.

title: ​820-2914 - Won't turn on
